title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant ex-sniper
postcontent: Up for consideration is a prime example of a war time relic. I have a 1943 Izhevsk Mosin Magan 91/30. Barrel is in great shape. All metal parts are original and matching. This particular rifle was one of the top shooters of the time when made. It was pulled off the line, drilled and tapped for a scope. There is evidence of these drill holes in the receiver. There is a very high chance this bad boy was on the front lines dishing out some commie justice to nazis. After the war, it was re-arsenaled. The scope was removed, the holes were filled is and the scope number was crossed off of the barrel. There was another stock put on it and it sat and waited for its chance to come back around. It was crated and sent to the States. I purchased it and loved shooting it. Still do. It was very well taken care of and is still in great shape. I am now looking to get rid of it. I love Mosins, but I really want a Remington Arsenal Mosin. I'm looking for $300. This is a great rifle, and shows the marks of being a sniper rifle. Could have seen action in Stalingrad. If it could only speak.
